rComments: I took Cog Science Philosophy with professor Stokes at the U of U. The hardest class I've ever taken, do not take this class unless you have a very sophisticated vocabulary and are a good writer. The grade in the class comes from 2 papers and a final test, his TA grades incredibly hard and unless you are confident in your Philos skills don't take.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Wouldnt recommend this class unless you are a philosophy student. Tough grader... likes to convey/explain things more complex than needed.
Two papers (55% of final grade), participation(5%), and one final exam (40%) I'm a Phil major and thought this class was a little tough. Lectures are cool, but he's really hard on papers.

The hottest professor the world has ever met. Get ready to meet an improved version of David Beckham with brains ;-)  His lectures are very inspirational, interesting, and the topics relatable so that you actually want to go to his lectures.

Incredible! I was reluctant taking a philosophy class (science student), but I was PLEASANTLY surprised; not only by his effort and knowledge, but by the fact that he actually made me fall in love with philosophy :)

Prof Stokes was super cool.  He makes a genuine effort to ensure the students understand what he's talking about.  Because his lectures are so fun, clear, and relatable, I actually loved attending his class.  He's a super hottie, so that factor helps with the class attendance record too.
Great professor. Really unique. Engages with the class and makes learning extremely enjoyable. Any class that it taught by him is sure to be a fantastic class.

He's great, really interested in what he's teaching. You can tell he takes the time to prepare his lectures and it makes you care more. He moves at a quick pace, so keeping up is crucial. Overall, he is definitely a prof that you'll enjoy!

very good lecturer. he's a friendly and funny prof and engages his students.he speaks clearly and he's easy to understand. i got 80s on my papers simply using his lecture slides which are short and sweet and easy to understand.
You don't have to find him attractive to enjoy the amount of intellectual engagement he takes you through. One of my favourite professors thus far.
easy to understand what he is saying

Had him for PHLA01, and PHLB07. He knows what he is talking about, he is not rude, he is funny, he is clear about what is on his exams and his evaluations may sometimes be tougher than expected. Overall, the best philosophy professor at UTSC.
He's really friendly, intelligent, makes the lectures really interesting, and the material relatable so that you actually want to go to his lectures...and it helps that he's kind of a hottie!

He is organized and clear. He simplifies the material in class so it's important to go to his lectures. His lectures are amusing and he relates the course material to examples that we can relate to (from the media, for example). Overall, his was one that I looked forward to!

Enthusiastic about Theory of Mind material and admittedly wants to "frustrate" all philosophy students.  Approachable and friendly during class and generally helpful but is never in his office. Responds to email very promptly. Very intelligent without being arrogant and tries to keep classes interesting. Overall, an excellent prof.
